description:
&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our team within our Neighbourhood Therapy teams in Barnsley and an exciting opportunity has arisen for a new Senior Therapy Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will work as part of a multi-disciplinary team across our Neighbourhood Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following initial assessment by a registered health care professional, you will exercise initiative and judgement in, care planning, goal setting, delivery, implementation, and evaluation of care&lt;strong&gt;, &lt;/strong&gt;working collaboratively and in partnership with others. You will contribute to enabling service users to reach their potentialand develop knowledge to promote holistic care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work in close liaison with the wider MDT and other community therapy and nursing areas, therefore excellent communication and time management skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The teams provide assessment, treatment and support within patient’s own homes, Independent Sector Care Homes and spot-purchased nursing care homes, based on patient need and dependency levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The use of a vehicle to undertake any necessary travel in connection with the duties of the post is essential along with the ability to work flexibly including shift work, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact; Jane Illingworth If you are interested in this exciting new opportunity and would like an informal discussion regarding this role please contact Jane Illingworth 01226 644559 / jane.illingworth@swyt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy may close early if sufficient applicants are received.&lt;/p&gt;
